      "side": 1,
      "message": "rename to GrBackendSurfaceMutableState.\n\nTBH I\u0027m not sure what GrBackendRT will look like for non GL in the new world. It honestly may become a GL only thing. In other backends there are a lot more objects tied to the layout of the Framebuffer/RenderPass attachments. Also we\u0027d still need the image itself to do memory barriers, copies, etc. I\u0027m not sure it makes as much sense in terms of what a client would want to even try to support a similar thing. I could even see for GL that we just use GrBackendSurface but maybe have two constructors one takes a texID the other and FBO.",
